<subSubSection id="C374652CFFDFFFB4D4CCF9DF0C36F921" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BD136A7FFDFFFB4D4CCF9DF0C36F921" blockId="34.[151,1437,1400,2039]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFDFFFB4D4CCF9DF0C16F91D" bold="true" box="[199,334,1652,1678]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Etymology.</emphasis>
The epithet is a noun in apposition honoring to Ticunas (Tikunas), indigenous people who live in Amazonian region.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C374652CFFDFFFB4D4CCF9170FE9F865" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BD136A7FFDFFFB4D4CCF9170FE9F865" blockId="34.[151,1437,1400,2039]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFDFFFB4D4CCF9170C1AF945" bold="true" box="[199,322,1724,1750]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D24FFDFFFB4D5B9F9170F02F945" authority="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Quijano, 2022" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Quijano" authorityYear="2022" box="[434,602,1724,1750]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Tenedos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ticuna" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFDFFFB4D5B9F9170F02F945" box="[434,602,1724,1750]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Tenedos ticuna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFDFFFB4D66AF9170FF8F945" bold="true" box="[609,672,1724,1750]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22957CEFFDFFFB4D66AF9170FF8F945" box="[609,672,1724,1750]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D24FFDFFFB4D770F91609BCF945" authority="Jocque &amp; Baert, 2002" authorityName="Jocque &amp; Baert" authorityYear="2002" box="[891,1252,1724,1751]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Tenedos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoeferi">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFDFFFB4D770F9160EBDF945" box="[891,997,1724,1750]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">T. hoeferi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF4B56FFDFFFB4D7E7F91709BCF945" author="Jocque, R. &amp; Baert, L." box="[1004,1252,1724,1751]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="67 - 173" refId="ref79332" refString="Jocque, R. &amp; Baert, L. (2002) A revision of the Neotropical spider genera Tenedos O. P. - Cambridge and Ishania Chamberlin (Araneae, Zodariidae). Bulletin de l'Institut Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique, Entomologie, 72, 67 - 173." type="journal article" year="2002">Jocqué &amp; Baert, 2002</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, by having a developed conductor (C) curved at prolateral side (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF4B56FFDFFFB4D6E8F94B094AF969" author="Jocque, R. &amp; Baert, L." box="[739,1042,1760,1787]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="67 - 173" refId="ref79332" refString="Jocque, R. &amp; Baert, L. (2002) A revision of the Neotropical spider genera Tenedos O. P. - Cambridge and Ishania Chamberlin (Araneae, Zodariidae). Bulletin de l'Institut Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique, Entomologie, 72, 67 - 173." type="journal article" year="2002">Jocqué &amp; Baert, 2002: 100</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 18B–C; figs 22A–D; 23A–B), but can be recognized by extremely curved conductor (C) at prolateral region; very short and apically pointed retrolateral tibial apophysis (RTA); bifid median apophysis (MA), very wide, flattened, procurved anterior branch (aMA) (
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFDFFFB4D4F9F8E70CD9F8F5" box="[242,385,1868,1894]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="36.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[231,1350,210,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-27@36.[231,1357,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 22. Tenedos ticuna sp. n. A–D. Male palp (MPUJ_ENT 0062000):A. Prolateral view. B. Retroventral view. C. Ventral view. D. Retrolateral view. E–F. Female epigyne (IAvH-I-3762): E. Ventral view. F. Dorsal view. Scale bars:A–B: 200µm; C–D: 500µm; E–F: 100µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520803" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520803/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Figs 22A–D</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFDFFFB4D580F8E70CB8F8F5" box="[395,480,1868,1894]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1683,1707]" captionTargetBox="[161,1421,194,1651]" captionTargetId="figure-19@37.[151,1436,181,1659]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 23. Tenedos ticuna sp. n. A–B. Male palp (MPUJ_ENT 0062000):A. Ventral view. B. Retrolateral view. C–D. Female epigyne (IAvH-I-3762): C. Ventral view. D. Dorsal view. Scale bars: A–B: 200µm; C–D: 500µm.Abbreviations:ApC, appendix of the conductor; aMA, anterior branch of the median apophysis; C, conductor; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; LB, lateral borders; MFP, median field plate; S, spermathecae; SR, seminal receptacles; T, tegulum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520807" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520807/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">23A–B</figureCitation>
). Females are similar those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D24FFDFFFB4D73EF8E609C2F8F5" authority="Jocque &amp; Baert, 2002" authorityName="Jocque &amp; Baert" authorityYear="2002" box="[821,1178,1868,1895]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Tenedos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoeferi">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFDFFFB4D73EF8E60EC7F8F5" box="[821,927,1868,1894]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">T. hoeferi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF4B56FFDFFFB4D7ADF8E709C2F8F5" author="Jocque, R. &amp; Baert, L." box="[934,1178,1868,1895]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="67 - 173" refId="ref79332" refString="Jocque, R. &amp; Baert, L. (2002) A revision of the Neotropical spider genera Tenedos O. P. - Cambridge and Ishania Chamberlin (Araneae, Zodariidae). Bulletin de l'Institut Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique, Entomologie, 72, 67 - 173." type="journal article" year="2002">Jocqué &amp; Baert, 2002</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D24FFDFFFB4D0DBF8E60CD7F819" authority="Jocque &amp; Baert, 2002" authorityName="Jocque &amp; Baert" authorityYear="2002" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Tenedos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrangulatus">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFDFFFB4D0DBF8E608C4F8F5" box="[1232,1436,1868,1894]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">T. quadrangulatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF4B56FFDFFFB4D49CF8DB0CD7F819" author="Jocque, R. &amp; Baert, L." box="[151,399,1904,1931]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="67 - 173" refId="ref79332" refString="Jocque, R. &amp; Baert, L. (2002) A revision of the Neotropical spider genera Tenedos O. P. - Cambridge and Ishania Chamberlin (Araneae, Zodariidae). Bulletin de l'Institut Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique, Entomologie, 72, 67 - 173." type="journal article" year="2002">Jocqué &amp; Baert, 2002</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, by wide seminal receptacles (SR), curved towards median septum of epigyne; knob-shaped median field plate (MFP) (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF4B56FFDFFFB4D5F9F83F0E7CF83D" author="Jocque, R. &amp; Baert, L." box="[498,804,1940,1967]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="67 - 173" refId="ref79332" refString="Jocque, R. &amp; Baert, L. (2002) A revision of the Neotropical spider genera Tenedos O. P. - Cambridge and Ishania Chamberlin (Araneae, Zodariidae). Bulletin de l'Institut Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique, Entomologie, 72, 67 - 173." type="journal article" year="2002">Jocqué &amp; Baert, 2002: 100</bibRefCitation>
, 116, fig. 18D–E, 33A–B; figs 22E–F; 23C–D), but can be distinguished by wider seminal receptacles, larger, rounded median field plate; rounded spermathecae (S), close to copulatory ducts (CD) (
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFDFFFB4D5B6F8770F1CF865" box="[445,580,2012,2038]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="36.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[231,1350,210,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-27@36.[231,1357,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 22. Tenedos ticuna sp. n. A–D. Male palp (MPUJ_ENT 0062000):A. Prolateral view. B. Retroventral view. C. Ventral view. D. Retrolateral view. E–F. Female epigyne (IAvH-I-3762): E. Ventral view. F. Dorsal view. Scale bars:A–B: 200µm; C–D: 500µm; E–F: 100µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520803" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520803/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Figs 22E–F</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFDFFFB4D644F8770FFDF865" box="[591,677,2012,2038]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1683,1707]" captionTargetBox="[161,1421,194,1651]" captionTargetId="figure-19@37.[151,1436,181,1659]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 23. Tenedos ticuna sp. n. A–B. Male palp (MPUJ_ENT 0062000):A. Ventral view. B. Retrolateral view. C–D. Female epigyne (IAvH-I-3762): C. Ventral view. D. Dorsal view. Scale bars: A–B: 200µm; C–D: 500µm.Abbreviations:ApC, appendix of the conductor; aMA, anterior branch of the median apophysis; C, conductor; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; LB, lateral borders; MFP, median field plate; S, spermathecae; SR, seminal receptacles; T, tegulum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520807" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520807/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">23C–D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
